The paper presents an improved version of the bat algorithm, a population metaheuristic, to solve the Traveling Salesman Problems. This makes it likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an improvement in the basic structure of the classic bat algorithm, which could make it relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The experimentation carried out in the study involves statistical tests, which could make it relevant to the Other Computer Science (cs.OH) sub-category. Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed algorithm with other metaheuristics, which could make it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
